00:08:44.123 --> 00:08:46.692 line:95%,end
Of course our kids do not
go to speakeasies or bars.

00:08:46.759 --> 00:08:48.394 line:95%,end
I don't know what a speakeasy is.

00:08:48.461 --> 00:08:52.865 line:95%,end
OK, a speakeasy, also called
a blind pig or blind tiger,

00:08:52.932 --> 00:08:55.234 line:95%,end
is an establishment that illegally

00:08:55.301 --> 00:08:57.303 line:95%,end
sells alcoholic beverages.

00:08:57.370 --> 00:09:01.340 line:95%,end
Such establishments came into
prominence in the United States

00:09:01.407 --> 00:09:02.975 line:95%,end
during the period known as Prohibition.

00:09:03.042 --> 00:09:04.210 line:95%,end
I don't go to any that are illegal.

00:09:04.277 --> 00:09:05.511 line:95%,end
1920 to 1933.

00:09:05.578 --> 00:09:06.979 line:95%,end
[laughter]

00:09:07.046 --> 00:09:08.981 line:95%,end
Oh, [inaudible] illegal.

00:09:09.048 --> 00:09:12.385 line:95%,end
At one point, Kelly,
alcohol was prohibited.

00:09:12.451 --> 00:09:16.088 line:95%,end
So that's why our kids have
never been to a speakeasy.

00:09:16.155 --> 00:09:17.723 line:95%,end
