00:19:23.529 --> 00:19:24.730 line:95%,end
Push.

00:19:24.796 --> 00:19:26.331 line:95%,end
She's very angelic.

00:19:26.398 --> 00:19:29.234 line:95%,end
She does these lyrical routines
that are so pretty.

00:19:33.105 --> 00:19:35.774 line:95%,end
Maddie is going to prove to everybody
that they don't know

00:19:35.841 --> 00:19:36.975 line:95%,end
who she is.

00:19:37.042 --> 00:19:38.777 line:95%,end
She's more than you think.

00:19:38.844 --> 00:19:40.445 line:95%,end
Hey, come on, Paige, Nia.

00:19:40.512 --> 00:19:42.281 line:95%,end
Now remember, girls, this is the duet.

00:19:42.347 --> 00:19:44.383 line:95%,end
You asked me to do it. I pulled it.

00:19:44.449 --> 00:19:46.552 line:95%,end
You've had two weeks to do this number,

00:19:46.618 --> 00:19:50.722 line:95%,end
so it should look twice as good
as Maddie's solo,

00:19:50.789 --> 00:19:52.291 line:95%,end
twice as good as Brooke's solo.

00:19:52.357 --> 00:19:54.159 line:95%,end
They've been doing their dances for a day.

00:19:54.226 --> 00:19:55.427 line:95%,end
You've had an entire week.

00:19:55.494 --> 00:19:56.495 line:95%,end
Let's go.

00:19:56.562 --> 00:19:59.965 line:5%,start
Yesterday, Nia and Paige came
to me and asked if they could do

00:20:00.032 --> 00:20:03.402 line:5%,start
last week's cancelled duet
in this week's competition.

00:20:03.869 --> 00:20:06.872 line:5%,start
I want to see the performance
before I make my final decision.

00:20:06.939 --> 00:20:08.507 line:95%,end
Does the routine look good?

00:20:08.574 --> 00:20:10.742 line:95%,end
I don't know,
but I'm giving them the opportunity.

00:20:10.809 --> 00:20:13.045 line:95%,end
So come on, girls, impress me.

00:20:13.512 --> 00:20:15.981 line:95%,end
Every time you do that kick,
get your leg higher.

00:20:16.048 --> 00:20:17.683 line:95%,end
You're not thinking.

00:20:17.749 --> 00:20:20.185 line:95%,end
That's what I'm saying, you guys want
to do this-- oh, we want to do the duet.

00:20:20.252 --> 00:20:21.787 line:95%,end
It's fun. We want to do it.

00:20:21.887 --> 00:20:23.288 line:95%,end
You cannot go out there

00:20:23.355 --> 00:20:26.391 line:95%,end
and look any less of a dancer than Maddie.

00:20:28.727 --> 00:20:30.462 line:95%,end
Oh, you want both of us?
She said both of us.

00:20:30.529 --> 00:20:32.864 line:95%,end
- She wants both of us down there.
- Oh, crap.

00:20:32.931 --> 00:20:36.335 line:5%,start
I think there should be closure to
last week's experience at the competition

00:20:36.401 --> 00:20:37.769 line:5%,start
and the girls should do the duet.

00:20:37.836 --> 00:20:41.707 line:5%,start
I think that would be a nice way
to resolve the situation.

00:20:41.773 --> 00:20:44.710 line:95%,end
Kind of do some Abby psychology,
thinking about how you're going

00:20:44.776 --> 00:20:46.011 line:95%,end
to approach this situation.

00:20:46.078 --> 00:20:49.081 line:95%,end
The girls have asked me about
during the duet this weekend.

00:20:49.147 --> 00:20:50.449 line:95%,end
So we're doing the duet?

00:20:50.515 --> 00:20:52.517 line:95%,end
Yes. You have to do it.

00:20:52.584 --> 00:20:53.619 line:95%,end
You're going to go out there
and you're going to do it.

00:20:53.685 --> 00:20:56.588 line:95%,end
But I explained to Nia
that I pulled the duet

00:20:56.655 --> 00:20:59.324 line:95%,end
because I could not have
that behavior go on.

00:20:59.391 --> 00:21:02.961 line:95%,end
Like you said a pyramid,
other things have happened in the past.

00:21:03.028 --> 00:21:05.864 line:95%,end
We can't go backwards,
and I'm not going to,

00:21:05.931 --> 00:21:08.267 line:95%,end
but I am going to go forward.

00:21:08.333 --> 00:21:12.771 line:95%,end
And going forward,
that behavior will not be tolerated.

00:21:12.838 --> 00:21:15.107 line:95%,end
The girls came.
They asked me.

00:21:15.173 --> 00:21:16.241 line:95%,end
Paige was part of it, too.

00:21:16.308 --> 00:21:17.776 line:95%,end
They wanted to do it.

00:21:17.843 --> 00:21:19.745 line:95%,end
So you know what you're
getting yourselves into.

00:21:19.811 --> 00:21:20.846 line:95%,end
You have to do it.

00:21:20.912 --> 00:21:24.182 line:95%,end
I don't care what the results are
for this competition, of this duet.

00:21:24.249 --> 00:21:27.686 line:95%,end
At this point, Nia has already won.

00:21:27.753 --> 00:21:29.521 line:95%,end
The duet is going on stage.

00:21:29.588 --> 00:21:31.490 line:95%,end
She's going to get to perform it.

00:21:31.556 --> 00:21:33.925 line:95%,end
And I see maturity in Nia.


00:21:33.992 --> 00:21:36.228 line:95%,end
They asked me to do it, sink or swim.

00:21:36.928 --> 00:21:38.563 line:95%,end
Hey, we're going to Florida.

00:21:38.630 --> 00:21:39.765 line:95%,end
There's sharks.

00:21:42.100 --> 00:21:43.568 line:95%,end
What's going on with you and Kel?

00:21:43.635 --> 00:21:45.704 line:95%,end
Have you had a chance
to sit down and work it out?

00:21:45.771 --> 00:21:50.175 line:95%,end
No, but I keep going back
to when Kelly wasn't here,

00:21:50.242 --> 00:21:52.110 line:95%,end
who was the biggest advocate
for her to come back?

00:21:52.177 --> 00:21:53.278 line:95%,end
I know.

00:21:53.345 --> 00:21:54.946 line:95%,end
I had a bad week.

00:21:55.013 --> 00:21:58.917 line:95%,end
I needed someone to call me
and she didn't call me.

00:21:58.984 --> 00:22:02.454 line:95%,end
I know, it's like a double
whammy that Kelly's mad at you.

00:22:02.521 --> 00:22:04.489 line:95%,end
Because let's face,
that would be her sitting here

00:22:04.556 --> 00:22:05.557 line:95%,end
consoling you.

00:22:05.624 --> 00:22:09.361 line:95%,end
My feelings are hurt
because when it was Kelly in my situation,

00:22:09.428 --> 00:22:10.696 line:95%,end
I was her biggest cheerleader.

00:22:10.762 --> 00:22:12.397 line:95%,end
So where do you go from here?

00:22:12.464 --> 00:22:15.133 line:95%,end
I mean, do you continue to not speak?

00:22:15.200 --> 00:22:16.268 line:5%,start
I don't know.

00:22:16.335 --> 00:22:19.471 line:5%,start
Last week was an extremely
hard week for me and Chloe.

00:22:19.538 --> 00:22:21.306 line:95%,end
And Melissa called me.

00:22:21.373 --> 00:22:22.374 line:95%,end
Holly called me.

00:22:22.441 --> 00:22:23.508 line:95%,end
Jill called me.

00:22:23.575 --> 00:22:24.710 line:95%,end
Kelly never called me.

00:22:26.945 --> 00:22:28.513 line:95%,end
I don't know. I am a mess.

00:22:28.580 --> 00:22:30.649 line:95%,end
I wasn't myself.

00:22:30.716 --> 00:22:32.117 line:95%,end
I left. I came back.

00:22:32.184 --> 00:22:33.251 line:95%,end
I felt more like myself.

00:22:33.318 --> 00:22:36.154 line:95%,end
But like I'm the snarky
bitch of the group.

00:22:36.221 --> 00:22:37.155 line:95%,end
I'm not the crier.

00:22:37.222 --> 00:22:41.393 line:95%,end
I'm not the emotional one,
and I feel so out of sorts.

00:22:41.460 --> 00:22:43.195 line:95%,end
I really feel like an outsider this week.

00:22:43.261 --> 00:22:45.530 line:95%,end
I think because the team
went to a competition,

00:22:45.597 --> 00:22:48.033 line:95%,end
they had all these experiences,
they had some crazy fight

00:22:48.100 --> 00:22:49.067 line:95%,end
with Cathy--

00:22:49.134 --> 00:22:51.403 line:95%,end
you know, life went on
without Christi and Chloe,

00:22:51.470 --> 00:22:53.472 line:95%,end
and I don't think anybody
really even missed us.

00:22:53.538 --> 00:22:55.073 line:95%,end
Girls, listen up.

00:22:55.140 --> 00:22:59.010 line:5%,start
If you want fame,
start paying right here, right now--

00:22:59.077 --> 00:23:03.515 line:5%,start
blood, sweat, sore muscles, callouses.

00:23:03.582 --> 00:23:06.818 line:95%,end
We went to a competition
and not one of my students

00:23:06.885 --> 00:23:08.320 line:95%,end
made the top 10?

00:23:08.387 --> 00:23:11.323 line:95%,end
That's never going to happen
to the Abby Lee Dance Company again.

00:23:11.390 --> 00:23:13.792 line:95%,end
This is going to be like bootie camp.

00:23:13.859 --> 00:23:15.394 line:95%,end
You're going to walk in here
and you're going to work,

00:23:15.460 --> 00:23:18.330 line:95%,end
and you're gonna work, and you're gonna
work even harder the next day.

00:23:18.397 --> 00:23:21.266 line:95%,end
The group is not where I want it to be.

00:23:21.333 --> 00:23:24.469 line:95%,end
I know it's been a long day,
but this number is nowhere

00:23:24.536 --> 00:23:25.937 line:95%,end
near competition-ready.

00:23:26.004 --> 00:23:27.773 line:95%,end
Lock the back knee in the lunge.

00:23:27.839 --> 00:23:30.075 line:95%,end
Oh, somebody's foot is flexed.

00:23:30.142 --> 00:23:32.644 line:95%,end
Whoa. What is she doing there? Get up.

00:23:32.711 --> 00:23:38.049 line:95%,end
Yo, blondie, you were gone
for a week, not a year.

00:23:38.116 --> 00:23:40.285 line:95%,end
If Abby doesn't come around
and at least give Chloe

00:23:40.352 --> 00:23:43.455 line:95%,end
the common respect of calling
her by her given name,

00:23:43.522 --> 00:23:45.257 line:95%,end
you know, I can't say that
I'm going to sit back

00:23:45.323 --> 00:23:46.758 line:95%,end
and just let it happen.

00:23:46.825 --> 00:23:48.026 line:95%,end
Moms, let's go.

00:23:48.093 --> 00:23:49.561 line:95%,end
Bring those costumes down.

00:23:49.628 --> 00:23:53.765 line:95%,end
Girls, we are leaving on
a plane tomorrow morning.

00:23:53.832 --> 00:23:56.001 line:95%,end
This is the third time we're changing it

00:23:56.067 --> 00:23:59.538 line:95%,end
because you couldn't do it
the first two times.

00:23:59.604 --> 00:24:02.107 line:95%,end
Blondie, we could all be home by now.

00:24:02.174 --> 00:24:05.243 line:95%,end
You know what?
My daughter has a name.

00:24:05.310 --> 00:24:06.445 line:95%,end
ABBY LEE MILLER: Not anymore in my book.

00:24:06.511 --> 00:24:08.213 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: Oh, yes she does.

00:24:08.280 --> 00:24:09.681 line:95%,end
She has a name, Abby.

00:24:09.748 --> 00:24:10.715 line:95%,end
So do you.

00:24:10.782 --> 00:24:11.750 line:95%,end
Starts with a B.


00:24:20.325 --> 00:24:22.060 line:5%,start
Come on, girls, let's go.

00:24:22.127 --> 00:24:24.596 line:95%,end
MELISSA: In10sity is a good
competition for us this week

00:24:24.663 --> 00:24:26.932 line:95%,end
because there's a lot of
intense feelings between Abby

00:24:26.998 --> 00:24:29.601 line:95%,end
and Christi, between Kelly and Christi.

00:24:29.668 --> 00:24:31.102 line:5%,start
So intense is the word this week.

00:24:31.870 --> 00:24:33.805 line:95%,end
Girls, remember, you are
in Fort Lauderdale.

00:24:33.872 --> 00:24:35.974 line:95%,end
I mean, these kids down here dance.

00:24:36.041 --> 00:24:39.811 line:95%,end
Dance is part of the culture,
so you need to really focus.

00:24:39.878 --> 00:24:41.446 line:95%,end
This is all about the technique.

00:24:42.147 --> 00:24:43.381 line:95%,end
You got it?

00:24:48.653 --> 00:24:50.222 line:95%,end
Whether I called one time or 10 times,

00:24:50.288 --> 00:24:51.990 line:95%,end
she should have called me back.

00:24:52.057 --> 00:24:53.658 line:95%,end
MELISSA: She never answers my calls, too.

00:24:53.725 --> 00:24:55.360 line:95%,end
I don't know what the problem is.

00:24:55.427 --> 00:24:57.195 line:95%,end
No. I don't think I did anything wrong.

00:24:57.262 --> 00:24:58.830 line:95%,end
I don't, either.

00:24:58.897 --> 00:25:00.932 line:95%,end
- Christi, you're awfully quiet.
- Where's that fire?

00:25:00.999 --> 00:25:03.068 line:95%,end
Where's that spunk?

00:25:03.134 --> 00:25:04.236 line:95%,end
All gone.

00:25:04.302 --> 00:25:05.670 line:95%,end
You're not a wallflower.

00:25:06.004 --> 00:25:07.839 line:95%,end
Maybe I turned over a new leaf.

00:25:09.841 --> 00:25:11.243 line:95%,end
Now, listen to me.

00:25:11.309 --> 00:25:14.145 line:95%,end
When you get out there,
it's your face that wins.

00:25:14.212 --> 00:25:16.815 line:95%,end
Everybody here has beautiful technique.

00:25:16.882 --> 00:25:19.150 line:95%,end
Nobody else has Maddie's face.

00:25:19.217 --> 00:25:20.919 line:95%,end
Girls, duet.

00:25:20.986 --> 00:25:22.721 line:95%,end
Paige, you don't need to be goofy.

00:25:22.787 --> 00:25:24.389 line:95%,end
It's fun. It's hot.

00:25:24.456 --> 00:25:25.757 line:95%,end
You should look beautiful.

00:25:25.824 --> 00:25:27.926 line:95%,end
You've got two weeks
to work on this routine.

00:25:27.993 --> 00:25:29.694 line:95%,end
They haven't really worked
on it for two weeks, Abby.

00:25:29.761 --> 00:25:32.230 line:95%,end
- They lied.
- I know, that's my point.

00:25:32.531 --> 00:25:35.033 line:95%,end
They don't self-motivate themselves.

00:25:35.100 --> 00:25:37.335 line:95%,end
- They don't get out there and work on it.
- When do you want them to work on it?

00:25:37.402 --> 00:25:39.504 line:95%,end
We had privates
but we weren't able to go to those,

00:25:39.571 --> 00:25:41.239 line:95%,end
but Maddie went to hers.

00:25:41.306 --> 00:25:42.774 line:95%,end
You're so jealous of that kid, oh my god.

00:25:42.841 --> 00:25:43.975 line:95%,end
I'm not jealous of Maddie.

00:25:44.042 --> 00:25:45.710 line:95%,end
You're jealous
that I'm talking to her,

00:25:45.777 --> 00:25:47.345 line:95%,end
that I'm telling you the same thing
that I tell her every week.

00:25:47.412 --> 00:25:49.447 line:95%,end
Because, Abby, we're
going on a couple after her.

00:25:49.514 --> 00:25:51.349 line:95%,end
You made sure her makeup was perfect,

00:25:51.416 --> 00:25:52.617 line:95%,end
her costume was perfect.

00:25:52.684 --> 00:25:54.653 line:95%,end
You haven't looked at these two at all.

00:25:54.719 --> 00:25:55.854 line:95%,end
Well, you handle her makeup.

00:25:55.921 --> 00:25:56.922 line:95%,end
She's your job.

00:25:57.188 --> 00:25:59.658 line:95%,end
KELLY: Well, maybe Melissa
should learn how to do makeup.

00:25:59.724 --> 00:26:01.459 line:95%,end
This is Melissa's job, too.

00:26:01.526 --> 00:26:03.395 line:95%,end
Melissa has never walked
into my studio and said,

00:26:03.461 --> 00:26:05.697 line:95%,end
my children are my job. Never.

00:26:05.764 --> 00:26:07.332 line:95%,end
I don't need a job.

00:26:07.399 --> 00:26:09.935 line:95%,end
I know.
Your kids still needs to point her feet.

00:26:10.001 --> 00:26:12.003 line:95%,end
That's your job, to teach them.

00:26:12.070 --> 00:26:14.539 line:95%,end
No. Money can't buy talent.

00:26:14.606 --> 00:26:17.275 line:5%,start
Kelly, you want Paige's duet pulled again,

00:26:17.342 --> 00:26:18.910 line:5%,start
two weeks in a row?

00:26:18.977 --> 00:26:21.479 line:95%,end
You want Brooke's solo to just disappear?

00:26:22.247 --> 00:26:23.782 line:95%,end
How about you ask Holly and Christi

00:26:23.848 --> 00:26:25.617 line:95%,end
what running their mouths got them?

00:26:25.684 --> 00:26:28.186 line:95%,end
[I suggest you shut up and sit down.

00:26:28.253 --> 00:26:30.221 line:95%,end
This is Brooke's first solo act.

00:26:30.488 --> 00:26:33.558 line:95%,end
We'll see if it's her
last solo on the team.

00:26:34.025 --> 00:26:37.162 line:95%,end
Girls, go out there and dance today

00:26:37.228 --> 00:26:39.264 line:95%,end
and don't make me sorry
that I let you do it.

00:26:39.564 --> 00:26:40.932 line:95%,end
Understand?

00:26:41.333 --> 00:26:42.634 line:5%,start
There is an elephant in the room,

00:26:42.701 --> 00:26:44.069 line:5%,start
and for once, it's not Abby.

00:26:44.636 --> 00:26:46.838 line:95%,end
Kelly and I have this huge feud going on,

00:26:46.905 --> 00:26:48.607 line:95%,end
and eventually we're going
to have to talk it out.

00:26:48.673 --> 00:26:49.841 line:95%,end
We can't keep going on like this.

00:26:51.142 --> 00:26:52.744 line:95%,end
I will talk to you as
soon as she's done dancing.

00:26:52.811 --> 00:26:55.614 line:95%,end
I want to get her out there
and then I'll talk to you, okay?

00:26:55.680 --> 00:26:57.015 line:95%,end
Mm-hmm.

